schema:description
Whole genome sequencing for G1 individuals, part of the UK10K dataset. UK10K_COHORT Release 2012-06-02 : v2 ==================================== Description =========== This release comprises phased genotype calls for 3781 UK10K COHORT samples from the following two studies: 1927 UK10K_COHORT_ALSPAC 1854 UK10K_COHORT_TWINSUK Calling and filtering are described in the README for v1. Sites which passed filters (see README for v1) were brought forward to genotype refinement. Samples were dropped after calling and before genotype refinement for reasons described below. UK10K_COHORT_TWINSUK 64 samples removed - 7 no GWAS data - 1 excessive het rate - 55 discordance > 3% - 1 coverage < 4x UK10K_COHORT_ALSPAC 48 samples removed - 1 excessive het rate - 36 discordance > 3% - 11 coverage < 4x Genotype refinement ------------------- The missing and low confidence genotypes were refined with BEAGLE 4, rev909 in chunks of 3,000 sites plus 1,000 sites in buffer regions. Multiallelic sites were included in the imputation. Further Sample exclusion ------------------------ Further samples were removed after genotype refinement based on the following criteria: UK10K_COHORT_TWINSUK 16 samples removed - 13 contamination - 12 NRD > 5% - 3 failed sex check UK10K_COHORT_ALSPAC 1 sample removed - 1 contamination - 1 NRD > 5% For downstream analysis a further 177 samples may be excluded due to non-European ancestry, or relatedness. A list of these samples is provided with the release. Annotations ----------- The calls were annotated using vcf-annotate and include dbSNP 137 rsIDs. Sites where different alternate allele of the same type (SNP vs indel) were found in the UK10K data have dbSNPmismatch flag in the INFO column. The 1000Genomes frequencies are taken from the final 1000 Genomes Phase 1 integrated (v3) callset available here: ftp://ftp.1000genomes.ebi.ac.uk//vol1/ftp/phase1/analysis_results/integrated_call_sets The files used for these annotations can be found on this sftp site /uk10k/ref/annots-rsIDs-dbSNPv137.2012-09-13.tab.gz /uk10k/ref/annots-rsIDs-AFs.2012-07-19.tab.gz on this sftp site. Functional Annotations ---------------------- Variant consequence annotations are called using the Ensembl Variant Effect Predictor (http://www.ensembl.org/info/docs/variation/vep/index.html), v2.6 against Ensembl 68. This provides coding consequence predictions and SIFT, PolyPhen and Condel annotations. Ensembl also provides GERP conservation scores. Grantham matrix values come from a simple lookup. The consequences are in the format: CSQ=ENSTid:Genename:consequence_string[:CDS_coord:Peptide_coord:AA>AA:Functional_annot,value]+ENSTid2:Genename:consequence_string2:...[+gerpScore] i.e. consequences are separated by '+', with each consequence containing ':' separated fields. Functional annotations (PolyPhen, etc) are given as name,value. Files ====== The release is split by chromosome. Each chromosome has a bgzipped VCF file (e.g. 21.beagle.anno.csq.20130126.vcf.gz) containing the phased genotype information and a corresponding VCF of the sites only (21.beagle.anno.csq.20130126.sites.vcf.gz). Each VCF has been indexed using tabix, with the index file having the .tbi extension (21.beagle.anno.csq.20130116.vcf.gz.tbi). There is also a stats file for each genotype VCF (21.beagle.anno.csq.20130116.vcf.gz.vchk) created using vcfcheck (see https://github.com/samtools/htslib). *.beagle.anno.csq.20130126.vcf.gz, *.beagle.anno.csq.20130126.vcf.gz.tbi, *.beagle.anno.csq.20130126.vcf.gz.vchk *.beagle.anno.csq.20130126.sites.vcf.gz, *.beagle.anno.csq.20130126.vcf.gz.tbi Based on non-European ancestry and relatedness 177 of the samples in this release should be excluded from certain downstream analysis. These samples are listed in this file: samples_for_exclusion.txt Information files. md5s.txt : md5 checksum of data files README : this file
